name: David Webster
text: Conveniently located off the main strip of Orange Beach. Paid parking garage on-site as part of the hotel structure. Lobby is located on the 4th floor with a beautiful view of the ocean. Lots of lobby seating with a small public balcony with tables and chairs. Front desk staff was always polite and helpful. Our room was comfortable and clean. Seldom heard a noise in the hallway or connecting rooms even though it was very busy (noises seemed to be insulated well). Swimming pool was busy with young kids most of the time, hot tub was closed or broke. Elevators always smelled clean but needed to be swept more often by staff (kids and adults constantly tracked sand in them). Bartenders by the pool were friendly. Easy access to the beach. Chairs and umbrellas available for rental by an outside company but didn't have any trouble using our own stuff. Hotel provides beach towels for guests at the front desk but they are thin and old. The hotel is located right next door to the public beach access which honestly made it seem less busy than some of the beach areas outside the larger condos and hotels. The beach outside this hotel never seemed over crowded. Breakfast in the morning had lots of options and tasted good. It was self-service buffet style while we were there. Employees wore masks but it was optional for guests. We always felt safe and comfortable. Honestly, we did have a nice stay. This hotel is VERY expensive for the services provided. They need more custodial cleaners by the pool area to keep it clean.

name: Kathy Mote
text:
The hotel common areas were clean. Our bed was comfortable.  The room was old, had stains on the carpet, and broken tiles in the shower. The spa didn't work and the pool was freezing. The staff were accommodating and very friendly.
Take the stairs when possible because the elevators are slow and very crowded.  I saw no sign of covid precautions except there is no maid service.
The price was outrageous - especially because of what I previously stated. There were no bikes as the website states. There was no seating area with a firepit.  The music was insanely loud at the pool. On the beach the rental company made anyone NOT renting from them seem like  they shouldn't even be on the beach(the HOTEL'S beach).
Ok, enough about the hotel, let's talk about the Town. Make sure you get to a restaurant by 4pm(3:30 is best) or you may not eat. Pizza delivery is a 2-3 hour wait...unless they run out of dough- yes, that happened. I'm not at all blaming the restaurants, they're doing all they can with what they have. It's just a circumstance you'll have to  deal with. Every. Single. Establishment is hiring. I do feel for them. Also pick at least 3 restaurants to head to because the 1st 3 just may be closed for lack of employees. There are too many people to accommodate everyone when all of the hotels are full. You take your life in your hands when driving.
Now let's talk about the beautiful Gulf water. Full of June Grass-look it up, it's disgusting, sticks to your skin, gets stuck in your bathing suit and stinks.
So August 17th -24th the gulf was not beautiful or blueish green,  It was thick and gross.

To the best of my knowledge, the staff also live on the property (so they are always there to assist...and they are always keeping an eye out, too.) The rooms are older and aren't very "up-to-date." But they have a pretty nice laundry room, and the weekly rates are very good. Despite the shortcomings, however, the rooms are very large and are definitely worth the prices. I *try* to stay at The Haven when I need a room quick and am low on funds. You definitely don't feel grimey after a night there, that's for sure.

In September 2020.

You are 5 minutes from downtown and the main strip that takes you to most of the restaurants and shopping in Wetumpka.

This place is a gem!

text:
The worst moving decision I ever made. I've been here for 6 months August 2018 and have experienced things I thought I would never experience. My first few months there was gunshots almost every night which I'm not used to so imagine staying somewhere sleeping and then hearing that and having to run get your child for safety! During my moving day, the apartment was a mess. The front door looked like someone kicked the door in and it took maintenance a month to just put wood filler and paint on the door and door frame instead of replacing it. The apartment was roach infested which I am not immune to so I was extremely on edge seeing the roaches were in the apartment and gnats taking over the kitchen. Their pest control did not resolve the issue at all. It took for me to buy over $30 worth of pest control products at Lowe's which helped a lot! The main light in the kitchen was not working and it took maintenance a month to switch it out so I was cooking and cleaning using the counter light because I refused to spend my own money on something they should be doing and still have to pay rent. Then, all the plugs in the living/dining room except for 2 is not working and 1 in my son bedroom is not working and maintenance have not come to resolve that issue till this day 02/28/19. The closet doors have been dislocated in all bedrooms and hall since I moved in and no one came to fix it till this day 02/28/19. Stayed in #22, terrible mistake. Stay far away from unit 22. Far far away, they took the listing off VRBO so we couldn’t leave a review there. The Cohen Family has done a TERRIBLE job of upkeep on this place. Going in, we knew it hasn’t been remodeled. That’s totally fine! But it was FILTHY. It’s got to be 6 months plus of dust on all the blinds, hanging picture frames, headboards. The shower curtains had mold, the toilets had dried urine spots, there was a dirty towel left in one of the bathrooms. The bed sheets seemed clean, but are so old they have holes. The bath towels are old. The microwave has broken plastic, the dishwasher leaks. The couches are so old and worn, the arm rests are discolored. The carpet wasn’t vacuumed, the tile in the kitchen has broken pieces with some grout missing.

David Cohen came and tried to vacuum right under foot with all our kids here. Wasn’t interested in seeing the issues. He was suppose to come the next day and clean while we were out, didn’t show up. I hope they refund us some money at least for the cleaning fee. We’ve left it no more dirty than it already was.

The beach itself was awesome, easy access. I’m so thankful the weather was perfect and were able to be out of this dump majority of the time.

WE IMMEDIATELY STARTED BAGGING EVERYTHING WE HAD BROUGHT INSIDE and packed as much of the food as we could shove in cracks in our vehicles...we then messaged the owner as we then leave the unit looking for a hotel to stay the night... THERE WAS NO VACANCY ANYWHERE YAL!!!! I CRIED!!! At 4am there was nothing else I could do... being out of town and not knowing what to do my 5, 10,& 12 yr old and i... and then my sister and her 11,10, and 1 yr old both slept in our vehicles front of a laundry mat until they opened so we could use the super dryers FOR ALL OF OUR STUFF which cost us 15$ each and walked to Walgreens and vought 2 cans of bug spray! We are both single moms who worked our buttons off to be able to make our girls birthday and our kids vacation a good one, but because the unit was infested not only was our vacation ruined we had to waist even MORE money on stuff we had no control of! Our kids were devastated... this being our first family vacation it will definitely be something we will never forget!
